The paper proposes a novel approach for Multi-Agent deep Reinforcement Learning (MARL) in partially observable and non-stationary environments. This suggests that the paper could belong to sub-categories such as Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), Game Theory (cs.GT), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The focus on regret minimization and Bayesian methods also supports these sub-categories.
